<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="26" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,259,1111]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,259,284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">Description.</emphasis>
Body brown and shining, eyes black, anterior part of vertex pale yellow medially (Fig. 
<number box="[1328,1359,260,284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="10.0">10</number>
). Face brown, frontal area pale (Fig. 
<number box="[489,520,295,319]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="12.0">12</number>
). Pronotum, scutum and scutellum dark brown, scutellum with apex yellow (Fig. 
<number box="[151,182,332,356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="10.0">10</number>
). Forewing brown, clavus with two large yellow patches, one nearly pentagonal and another triangular, with brown fascia between them, brochosome field with elliptical red patch (Figs. 
<number box="[1026,1098,367,391]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="10.11">10, 11</number>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[1120,1176,367,391]" name="India" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">Hind</collectingCountry>
wing transparent, with brown veins (
<figureCitation box="[304,388,404,428]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 56" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1933,1956]" captionTargetBox="[211,1387,208,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[179,1403,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 56. Zyginella petala sp. nov. 48. Male genital capsule, lateral view; 49. Forewing; 50. Hind wing; 51. Connective; 52. Apical part of subgenital plate; 53. Paramere; 54. Subgenital plate; 55. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 56. Aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/213313/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">
Fig. 
<number box="[356,388,404,428]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="50.0">50</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,259,1111]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">
Male genital capsule short, pygophore side acute, with short, sclerotized process internally and posteroventrally, and with spine-like process dorsally, with seven long macrosetae postero-dorsally and several small setae along posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[425,511,511,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 56" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1933,1956]" captionTargetBox="[211,1387,208,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[179,1403,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 56. Zyginella petala sp. nov. 48. Male genital capsule, lateral view; 49. Forewing; 50. Hind wing; 51. Connective; 52. Apical part of subgenital plate; 53. Paramere; 54. Subgenital plate; 55. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 56. Aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/213313/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">
Fig. 
<number box="[479,511,511,535]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="48.0">48</number>
</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate parallel-sided, with apex long and narrow, abruptly curved laterad, with two macrosetae and a few microsetae subapically (
<figureCitation box="[844,983,548,572]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 56" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1933,1956]" captionTargetBox="[211,1387,208,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[179,1403,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 56. Zyginella petala sp. nov. 48. Male genital capsule, lateral view; 49. Forewing; 50. Hind wing; 51. Connective; 52. Apical part of subgenital plate; 53. Paramere; 54. Subgenital plate; 55. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 56. Aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/213313/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">
Figs. 
<number box="[908,983,548,572]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="52.54">52, 54</number>
</figureCitation>
). Paramere with long, tapering bent apical part and with numerous thin setae subapically (
<figureCitation box="[728,813,583,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 56" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1933,1956]" captionTargetBox="[211,1387,208,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[179,1403,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 56. Zyginella petala sp. nov. 48. Male genital capsule, lateral view; 49. Forewing; 50. Hind wing; 51. Connective; 52. Apical part of subgenital plate; 53. Paramere; 54. Subgenital plate; 55. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 56. Aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/213313/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">
Fig. 
<number box="[782,813,583,607]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="53.0">53</number>
</figureCitation>
). Connective short, V-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1162,1246,583,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 56" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1933,1956]" captionTargetBox="[211,1387,208,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[179,1403,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 56. Zyginella petala sp. nov. 48. Male genital capsule, lateral view; 49. Forewing; 50. Hind wing; 51. Connective; 52. Apical part of subgenital plate; 53. Paramere; 54. Subgenital plate; 55. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 56. Aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/213313/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">
Fig. 
<number box="[1215,1246,583,607]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="51.0">51</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with preatrium long and dorsal apodeme well-developed; shaft long, with two rows of small teeth on lateral margin of midlength, with five fingerlike processes apically, resembling petals of a flower; gonopore apical (
<figureCitation box="[1252,1390,655,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 56" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1933,1956]" captionTargetBox="[211,1387,208,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[179,1403,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 56. Zyginella petala sp. nov. 48. Male genital capsule, lateral view; 49. Forewing; 50. Hind wing; 51. Connective; 52. Apical part of subgenital plate; 53. Paramere; 54. Subgenital plate; 55. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 56. Aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/213313/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">
Figs. 
<number box="[1316,1390,655,679]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="55.56">55, 56</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,259,1111]" box="[201,723,692,716]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,352,692,716]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">Body length.</emphasis>
2.64–2.80 mm (including wing).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
