<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="26" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,259,1111]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,316,836,860]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[637,766,837,860]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Zyginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctata">
<emphasis box="[637,766,837,860]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">Z. punctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<number box="[781,841,836,860]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="1985.0">1985</number>
), but differs in the pentagonal and triangular patches of the forewing clavus and the red patch of the brochosome field (Figs. 
<number box="[957,1028,871,895]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="10.11">10, 11</number>
); 
<taxonomicName box="[1051,1178,873,896]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Zyginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctata">
<emphasis box="[1051,1178,873,896]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">Z. punctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a continuous large patch on the forewing clavus and a black patch on the brochosome field (Figs. 
<number box="[1046,1120,908,932]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="16.17">16, 17</number>
). In male genitalia it can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[368,495,945,968]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Zyginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctata">
<emphasis box="[368,495,945,968]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">Z. punctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of a long serrated subapical process of the subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[1338,1431,943,967]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 56" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1933,1956]" captionTargetBox="[211,1387,208,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[179,1403,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 56. Zyginella petala sp. nov. 48. Male genital capsule, lateral view; 49. Forewing; 50. Hind wing; 51. Connective; 52. Apical part of subgenital plate; 53. Paramere; 54. Subgenital plate; 55. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 56. Aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/213313/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">
Figs. 
<number box="[1401,1431,943,967]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="54.31">54</number>
</figureCitation>
, 31), by presence of two rows of teeth on the lateral margin of the aedeagus near the midlength and by the fingerlike apical processes of the aedeagal shaft, all absent in 
<taxonomicName box="[775,903,1017,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Zyginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctata">
<emphasis box="[775,903,1017,1040]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">Z. punctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[918,1054,1015,1039]" captionStart="FIGURES 48 – 56" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1933,1956]" captionTargetBox="[211,1387,208,1876]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[179,1403,193,1888]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 48 – 56. Zyginella petala sp. nov. 48. Male genital capsule, lateral view; 49. Forewing; 50. Hind wing; 51. Connective; 52. Apical part of subgenital plate; 53. Paramere; 54. Subgenital plate; 55. Aedeagus, dorsal view; 56. Aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/213313/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">
Figs. 
<number box="[981,1054,1015,1039]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="55.56">55, 56</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<number box="[1065,1138,1015,1039]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" value="32.33">32, 33</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="26" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,259,1111]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1052,1076]" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin word “ 
<taxonomicName box="[933,1003,1052,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Zyginella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petala">
<emphasis box="[933,1003,1052,1076]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="26">petala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, referring to the petal-like apical part of aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
